arStrings.szText: Two shadowy jaguar spirits are killing travelers on the road

Ah-Comotl, a wandering exile, is the only survivor after a group of travelers were butchered by two spirit jaguars. The exile now seeks my help to confront the beasts. 

At a nearby temple, Ah-Comotl will try to summon the creatures but only a skilled warrior like myself has any hope of defeating them.
We have reached the old temple where Ah-Comotl will try to summon the spirit jaguars for me to slay. I should speak with him.
Ah-Comotl's ritual is complete and the spirit jaguars are upon us! I must kill them before they vanish once again.

The beasts we fought were Ah-Comotl's sons, transformed into hideous monsters by the Laughing Midnight Jaguar, the spirit who tricked the exile all those years ago.

Ah-Comotl mourns before his son's corpses. I should attempt to speak with him before I leave.
We have reached the old temple where Ah-Comotl will try to summon the spirit jaguars for me to slay. I should speak with him.
We have reached the old temple where Ah-Comotl will try to summon the spirit jaguars for me to slay. I should speak with him.
We have reached the old temple where Ah-Comotl will try to summon the spirit jaguars for me to slay. I should speak with him.

I learned that the spirit jaguar's master is an old enemy of the exile I travel with. Ah-Comotl, the exile, was tricked by the creature into losing his sons.

Ah-Comotl has begun the ritual summon the spirit jaguars for me to slay. I should prepare.
We have reached the old temple where Ah-Comotl will try to summon the spirit jaguars for me to slay. I should speak with him.
